e old border game but more difficult to manage, with more players, played out on a bigger stage, and with higher stakes and collateral damage.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aBorder patrolsxMexican-American Border Region. 0aBorder patrolszMexican-American Border Region. 0aBoundaries. 0aDrug controlzUnited States. 0aDrug trafficxGovernment policyxUnited States. 0aDrug trafficxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aIllegal aliensxGovernment policyxUnited States. 0aIllegal aliensxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aSmugglingxMexican-American Border Region. 0aSmugglingzMexican-American Border Region. 4aCriminology. 4aLegal History & Studies. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 7aLAW / Legal History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978080145829340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780801458293423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780801458293.jpg  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK